"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>\u003C!--commented out pending revision-->\n                    \u003C!--- - -okl | chaire. T insists in both eds. on reading oklei, but as SEG (first Moretti, then Tybout) observe, no visible sign of these letters in the photo (and I'd agree). T originally dated to C1-2 AD, but Moretti, SEG 34.949 thought earlier, and C1 BC date now offered in Tullio 1993 (fits with e.g. CIL simply comments: 'Tauromenii in curte diversorii Bellevue', i.e. in the courtyard of the building called Bellevue.he Lipari funerary stuff as C1 BC). ; cf. also Tullio, Akten des XIII Internationalen Kongresses fur klassiche archaeologie (1990), p.429-30.-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"SEG\">\n                        \u003CcitedRange>58.1045\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"SEG\">\n                        \u003CcitedRange>43.0625\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"SEG\">\n                        \u003CcitedRange>34.0949\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F2GG87EQ\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n